# ==== Commit Message Format ====
# <type>(<scope>)[CBDB-<issue_id>]: <subject>
# 
# <optional body>
# 
# <optional footer>

# ==== Full Example ====
# feat(auth)[CBDB-42]: implement user registration flow
# fix(database)[CBDB-17]: resolve connection pooling leak
# docs(readme)[CBDB-89]: update project setup instructions

# ==== Commit Type Prefixes ====
# 🆕 feat:     A new feature
# 🐛 fix:      A bug fix
# 📝 docs:     Documentation only changes
# 🎨 style:    Formatting, missing semi colons, etc; no code change
# 🔨 refactor: Refactoring production code
# 🚀 perf:     A code change that improves performance
# 🧪 test:     Adding missing tests or correcting existing tests
# 🛠 chore:    Maintenance tasks, updates to build process
# 🔒 security: Security-related changes

# ==== CBDB Specific Guidance ====
# - Project ID is MANDATORY
# - Use CBDB-<number> format
# - Keep total subject line under 72 characters
# - Use imperative mood
# - Capitalize first letter
# - No period at end of subject line
